extends ../../layout

append styles
  style
    body {
      background-color: #fff;
      color: #333;
      font: 1em / 1.4 Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 1em;
      margin: 0;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

block content
  h2 HTML5 controls
  section
    h3 Task 1
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_HTML5_controls")
      p First let's explore some of the new HTML5 input types. Create appropriate inputs for a user to update their details for:
      ol
        li Email
        li Website
        li Phone number
        li Favourite color
    form
      h2 Edit your preferences
      ul 
        li 
          label(for="e-mail") Email
          input#e-mail(type="email" name="email")
        li 
          label(for="website") Website
          input#website(type="url" name="url")
        li 
          label(for="phone") Phone number
          input#phone(type="tel" name="tel")
        li 
          label(for="fav-color") Favorite color
          input#fav-color(type="color" name="color")
        li 
          button(type="submit") Update preferences
  
  section
    h3 Task 2
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_HTML5_controls")
      p Next, we want you to implement a slider control to allow the user to choose a maximum number of people to invite to their party.
      ol 
        li Implement a basic slider control to go along with the provided label.
        li Give it a minimum value of 1, maximum value of 30, and initial value of 10.
        li Create a corresponding output element to put the current value of the slider into. Give it a class of #[code invite-output], and semantically associate it with the input. If you do this correctly, the JavaScript included on the page will automatically update the output value when the slider is moved.
    form
      ul
        li 
          label(for="max-invite") 
          input#max-invite(type="range", name="invitations", min="1", max="30", "value="10")
          output.invite-output(for="max-invite")
        li 
          button(type="submit") Submit
    script
      - const invite = document.querySelector('#max-invite');
      - const output = document.querySelector('.invite-output');

      - output.textContent = invite.value;

      - invite.addEventListener('input', function() {
        output.textContent = invite.value;
      });